# =============================================================================
# CREDENTIAL SAFETY — defensive against accidental token/PAT commits
# =============================================================================
# Even though *.key / *.pem are typically already covered, name common
# credential-store filenames explicitly so `git add ../<name>` from a sibling
# repo or `git add -A` from a parent dir cannot drag them in. Real secrets
# should live in Windows Credential Manager / Keychain, never on disk.
**/completerepoaccess*
**/dev_token
**/.git-credentials
**/aws*key*
**/aws_credentials
**/comfyuiapikey*
**/github_pat*
**/*_pat.txt
**/*.pat
**/civitai*key*
**/huggingface*token*
**/anthropic*key*
**/openai*key*
